reset links via HTTPS.\n148 |     *   Ensure the password reset API does not disclose user existence (preventing account enumeration attacks).\n149 |     *   Record and log password update events within the audit trail.\n150 | \n151 | ### 3.5. Production Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA) & Enterprise SSO\n152 | *   **Action Plan**: Replace the high-fidelity MFA simulations with real server-side cryptographic verification and Enterprise Single Sign-On (SSO) systems.\n153 | *   **Security Protocols**:\n154 |     *   **TOTP Verification**: Implement standard server-side verification using standard algorithms (RFC 6238) compatible with Google Authenticator, Microsoft Authenticator, or Bitwarden.\n155 |     *   **Federated Identity**: Integrate SAML 2.0 / OpenID Connect (OIDC) protocols to support corporate identity providers (such as Okta, Microsoft Entra ID / Active Directory, Ping Identity, and Duo).\n156 | ","success":true}],"durationMs":5}}
